history.content: @3831 explains how discussion sections are being registered this semester. Basically, students won't be enrolling in a discussion section until the semester starts. They encourage us to go on courses.berkeley.edu, look up the class, find the discussion section listings, and just mark off in your personal calendar which one you'd prefer taking, and the professor will address discussion session attendance in detail on a case by case basis.

there was an issue with adding the discussion sections for CS 189 during Phase 1 registration. Currently on CalCentral, I am enrolled in CS 189 lecture, but the discussion section shows up as "-". At the time, we had been told to just wait. Is there anything we should do now, or should we just wait until school starts and we get further instructions?
